"Block lookup, large-static-literal benchmark (workload class E). GENERATED by gen/gen_020_lookup_curve.py -- do not edit by hand. Freezes the W3 lookup-evidence spike (report 2026-07-12-w3-lookup): static-literal blocks of 40 and 250 keys hit by saturated dynamic lookup (16 keys/iteration). The bytecode engine walks an interpreted linear find loop (index gated off); HeapSyn builds/reuses a key index (>=16-key threshold), so bc is dramatically slower here -- a regression tripwire for the index decision (eu-4zhi), not a real-workload win. Runs >1s on the faster engine (bc-dominated by N=250)."

